===Noun===
'''milkshake'''  (''plural:'' '''[[milkshakes]]''')
# A thick beverage consisting of milk and [[ice cream]] mixed together, often with fruit, chocolate, or other flavoring.
# (''non-standard''): A beverage consisting of fruit juice, water, and some milk, as served in Southeast Asia.
# Slang for a sexual characteristic or appeal, such as in the phrase, "My milkshake brings all the boys to the yard."  Signifying whoredom and prostitution of one's body, though some (mainly black) cultures seem to take pride in such milkshakes.

